_KEEP_ASPECT''' = '''4'''  Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, but maintain the texture's aspect ratio.*  '''STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_CENTERED''' = '''5'''  Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, center it, and maintain its aspect ratio.*  '''STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_COVERED''' = '''6'''  Scale the texture so that the shorter side fits the bounding rectangle. The other side clips to the node's limits.== Property Descriptions ===== expand ===*  bool '''expand'''{| class="wikitable | ''Default''|| {{Span|false}}         |-| ''Setter''|| set_expand(value) |-| ''Getter''|| get_expand()      |}If {{Span|true}}, the texture stretches to the edges of the node's bounding rectangle using the [[#stretch_mode|stretch_mode]]. If {{Span|false}}, the texture will not scale with the node.=== stretch_mode ===*  [[#StretchMode|StretchMode]] '''stretch_mode'''{| class="wikitable | ''Default''|| {{Span|0}}                   |-| ''Setter''|| set_stretch_mode(value) |-| ''Getter''|| get_stretch_mode()      |}Controls the texture's behavior when you resize the node's bounding rectangle, '''only if''' [[#expand|expand]] is {{Span|true}}. Set it to one of the [[#StretchMode|StretchMode]] constants. See the constants to learn more.=== texture_click_mask ===*  [[BitMap GD|BitMap]] '''texture_click_mask'''{| class="wikitable | ''Setter''|| set_click_mask(value) |-| ''Getter''|| get_click_mask()      |}Pure black and white [[BitMap GD|BitMap]] image to use for click detection. On the mask, white pixels represent the button's clickable area. Use it to create buttons with curved shapes.=== texture_disabled ===*  [[Texture2D GD|Texture2D]] '''texture_disabled'''{| class="wikitable | ''Setter''|| set_disabled_texture(value) |-| ''Getter''|| get_disabled_texture()      |}Texture to display when the node is disabled. See [[BaseButton GD#disabled|BaseButton.disabled()]].=== texture_focused ===*  [[Texture2D GD|Texture2D